<dl id="n11026c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n11" href="#n11026c">N11 (VI.B.5)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n11all.htm#n11026c"> 26(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> <font color="green">[flag]</font> practice</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">A la troisi&egrave;me aurore, Vell&eacute;da monta sur mon char pour aller chercher S&eacute;genax. Elle avait &agrave; peine disparu dans les bois de ch&ecirc;nes que je vis s&apos;&eacute;lever au-dessus des for&ecirc;ts une colonne de feu et de fum&eacute;e. A l&apos;instant o&ograve; je d&eacute;couvrais ces signaux, un centurion vint m&apos;apprendre qu&apos;on entendait retentir de village en village les cris que poussent les Gaulois quand ils veulent se communiquer une nouvelle. <br><font color="green">[At the third dawn, Velleda climbed on my chariot to fetch S&eacute;genax. She had scarcely disappeared in the woods of oaks, when I saw a column of fire and smoke rising above the forests. At the moment when I discovered these signals, a centurion came to inform me that one could hear from village to village the cries that the Gauls give when they want to communicate news.]</font> <small> Chateaubriand, <a name="CHBD" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#CHBD"><cite title="source">&OElig;uvres choisies illustr&eacute;es</cite></a> (1912) II, <i>Les Martyrs</i> 82</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
